Of Monday) | $66,131 | Consolidate | Optimize | Y |\n    42→| Bisley Law Ltd | $67,414 | Consolidate | Optimize | Y |\n    43→| Cloud Technology Solutions Ltd | $60,661 | Consolidate | Optimize | Y |\n    44→| Wework Singapore Pte. Ltd. | ~$50K | Consolidate | Optimize | Y |\n    45→| Tmforum | ~$50K | Consolidate | Optimize | Y |\n    46→| Hr Solution International Pte. Ltd. | ~$50K | Consolidate | Optimize | Y |\n    47→\n    48→**9 of 13 Score-4 vendors are currently \"Consolidate\" but should be \"Optimize\"**\n    49→\n    50→## Key Conflict Tiers for Step 09\n    51→\n    52→### Tier A — Score 4 Consolidate → Optimize (9 vendors): HIGH PRIORITY\n    53→Vendors with significant switching cost being under-classified. Recommend upgrading all 9.\n    54→\n    55→### Tier B — Score 3 Terminate → Consolidate (11 vendors): MEDIUM PRIORITY\n    56→Key: Amazon Web Services Inc. (separate entity, Engineering), Sage UK (Finance software),\n    57→Grant Thornton (advisory), SS&C Intralinks (M&A data room), Vector Capital (M&A advisory),\n    58→Croatian telecom: Hrvatski Telekom, Telemach Hrvatska, New Star Networks.\n    59→\n    60→### Tier C — Score 2 Terminate → Consolidate (167 vendors): SYSTEMATIC FINDING\n    61→Over-termination pattern: 167 Score-2 vendors terminated without consolidation evaluation.\n    62→Many are insurance, SaaS tools, local professional services — marginal but non-zero value.\n    63→Step 09 should flag this as a governance gap (no preferred-supplier program in place).\n    64→\n    65→## Step 09 Use\n    66→\n    67→1. Upgrade 9 Consolidate→Optimize vendors (Tier A) in final recommendation\n    68→2. Salesforce + AWS = Score 5 confirmed; anchor Step 09 strategy around protecting these\n    69→3. 187 conflicts = 48% misalignment — cite as portfolio governance issue in strategy memo\n    70→4. Tier B telecom/audit consolidation = quick win for cost reduction narrative\n    71→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider