| Y |\n| Zagrebtower D.O.O. | ~$83K | Consolidate | Optimize | Y |\n| Weking D.O.O. | ~$70K | Consolidate | Optimize | Y |\n| Gpt Space & Co | ~$65K | Consolidate | Optimize | Y |\n| Big Frontier Pty Ltd (Cult Of Monday) | $66,131 | Consolidate | Optimize | Y |\n| Bisley Law Ltd | $67,414 | Consolidate | Optimize | Y |\n| Cloud Technology Solutions Ltd | $60,661 | Consolidate | Optimize | Y |\n| Wework Singapore Pte. Ltd. | ~$50K | Consolidate | Optimize | Y |\n| Tmforum | ~$50K | Consolidate | Optimize | Y |\n| Hr Solution International Pte. Ltd. | ~$50K | Consolidate | Optimize | Y |\n\n**9 of 13 Score-4 vendors are currently \"Consolidate\" but should be \"Optimize\"**\n\n## Key Conflict Tiers for Step 09\n\n### Tier A — Score 4 Consolidate → Optimize (9 vendors): HIGH PRIORITY\nVendors with significant switching cost being under-classified. Recommend upgrading all 9.\n\n### Tier B — Score 3 Terminate → Consolidate (11 vendors): MEDIUM PRIORITY\nKey: Amazon Web Services Inc. (separate entity, Engineering), Sage UK (Finance software),\nGrant Thornton (advisory), SS&C Intralinks (M&A data room), Vector Capital (M&A advisory),\nCroatian telecom: Hrvatski Telekom, Telemach Hrvatska, New Star Networks.\n\n### Tier C — Score 2 Terminate → Consolidate (167 vendors): SYSTEMATIC FINDING\nOver-termination pattern: 167 Score-2 vendors terminated without consolidation evaluation.\nMany are insurance, SaaS tools, local professional services — marginal but non-zero value.\nStep 09 should flag this as a governance gap (no preferred-supplier program in place).\n\n## Step 09 Use\n\n1. Upgrade 9 Consolidate→Optimize vendors (Tier A) in final recommendation\n2. Salesforce + AWS = Score 5 confirmed; anchor Step 09 strategy around protecting these\n3. 187 conflicts = 48% misalignment — cite as portfolio governance issue in strategy memo\n4. Tier B telecom/audit consolidation = quick win for cost reduction narrative\n","numLines":71,"startLine":1,"totalLines":71}}}
