{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01RjXsh9ksGTCniRdYJyp5nQ","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→---\n     2→name: STEP 07 Consolidation Opportunity Analysis\n     3→description: STEP 07 consolidation analysis: 23 opportunity groups, ~$6.89M combined spend in scope across 4 priority tiers; CRM ($3.16M) is #1; use in STEP 09 strategy recommendations\n     4→type: project\n     5→---\n     6→\n     7→STEP 07 identified 23 consolidation opportunity groups across 118 vendor entries. Total spend in scope: ~$6,899,005 (note: Allianz $7,069 counted in both Group 6 and Group 22; adjusted ~$6,892K unique spend).\n     8→\n     9→**Why:** Vendor master has duplicate AP entities, same-vendor product overlap, functional platform duplication, and unchecked agency/office proliferation.\n    10→**How to apply:** Reference these groups in STEP 09 strategy recommendations. P1 groups (≥$200K) are immediate CFO-level actions; P2/P3 feed the 90-day vendor review roadmap; P4 is hygiene cleanup.\n    11→\n    12→---\n    13→\n    14→## Priority Tier 1 — Combined Spend ≥ $200K (Groups 1–7, ~$5,668,677)\n    15→\n    16→1. **CRM & Sales Engagement** — $3,156,660\n    17→   - Salesforce UK ($3,117,226) + Cognism ($27,013) + Outreach Corp ($9,206) + Lusha ($2,606) + D&B ($610)\n    18→   - Retain Salesforce; consolidate Cognism/Outreach/Lusha into Salesforce-native tools or single sales-intelligence vendor; ~$39K overlap spend to eliminate\n    19→\n    20→2. **Office Space & Real Estate** — $827,834\n    21→   - TOG UK ($263,821) + Zagrebtower ($183,754) + Innovent Spaces ($147,348) + GPT Space ($133,507) + WeWork SG ($64,373) + JLL ($16,274) + Work Easy ($14,913) + Common Desk ($3,842)\n    22→   - Appoint JLL as strategic real estate manager; rationalise co-working agreements; exit underutilised flex sites\n    23→\n    24→3. **Travel & Expense — Navan Duplicate** — $415,913\n    25→   - Navan/TripActions Inc ($357,984) + Navan Inc ($57,929)\n    26→   - IMMEDIATE: same vendor, two AP entities — consolidate to single Navan contract; renegotiate on combined $416K volume\n    27→\n    28→4. **Audit & Accounting** — $412,219\n    29→   - BDO LLP ($343,081) + Grant Thornton ($46,539) + Granttree ($13,659) + PwC ($4,879) + Crowe Horwath ($4,062)\n    30→   - Retain BDO as primary statutory auditor; consolidate advisory to BDO; retain Granttree for R&D credits only\n    31→\n    32→5. **Cloud Infrastructure** — $390,710\n    33→   - Cloudcrossing BVBA ($208,675) + AWS LLC ($106,399) + Cloud Technology Solutions ($60,661) + Microsoft Ireland ($9,822) + AWS Inc. ($5,153)\n    34→   - Consolidate AWS LLC + Inc to single contract (duplicate entity); clarify Cloudcrossing scope vs native AWS; define AWS vs Azure strategy\n    35→\n    36→6. **Employee Health Insurance** — $238,406\n    37→   - Aetna ($124,661) + Agram Life ($24,952) + Care Health ($24,045) + Bupa-Supplier ($22,800) + Cigna SG ($13,249) + Bupa Australia ($12,463) + Allianz AU ($6,099) + ICICI Lombard ($5,972) + Cici Prudential ($3,195) + Allianz WA ($971)\n    38→   - Merge Bupa Supplier + Bupa Australia; merge Allianz AU + WA entities (see Group 22); engage global benefits broker for coordination\n    39→\n    40→7. **Financial & M&A Advisory** — $226,932\n    41→   - RSM UK Corporate Finance ($117,078) + SS&C Intralinks ($39,966) + Houlihan Lokey ($37,461) + Vector Capital ($32,427)\n    42→   - Project-based; consolidate VDR to SS&C Intralinks; rationalise M&A advisors to preferred panel; verify ongoing need post-deal\n    43→\n    44→---\n    45→\n    46→## Priority Tier 2 — Combined Spend $100K–$200K (Groups 8–14, ~$983,872)\n    47→\n    48→8. **HR Outsourcing & Payroll** — $161,708\n    49→   - HR Solution GmbH ($80,823) + Harmonic Group ($65,418) + HRSolution AG ($6,987) + Mercer ($5,444) + NCC Services ($3,036)\n    50→   - Consolidate HRSolution GmbH + AG (same brand, two legal entities); evaluate Harmonic vs HRSolution geographic overlap; target single global HR/payroll provider\n    51→\n    52→9. **Marketing Automation & Digital Advertising** — $161,420\n    53→   - LinkedIn Ireland ($55,573) + HubSpot Ireland ($32,187) + Uberflip ($26,091) + Google Ireland ($24,798) + MightyHive ($19,042) + Semrush ($3,730)\n    54→   - Retain HubSpot as primary; evaluate Uberflip vs HubSpot Content Hub (eliminate overlap); rationalise MightyHive as agency layer\n    55→\n    56→10. **Insurance Brokerage** — $152,800\n    57→    - Jensten Insurance Brokers ($142,700) + Shoff Darby Companies ($10,100)\n    58→    - Consolidate to single broker; Jensten as primary; negotiate combined policy portfolio discount\n    59→\n    60→11. **Telecoms & Connectivity** — $147,712\n    61→    - Telefonica Global ($89,880) + New Star Networks ($23,887) + Hrvatski Telekom ($18,084) + Telemach Hrvatska ($5,134) + Vodafone AU ($3,672) + T-Mobile ($3,357) + Starhub ($2,205) + British Telecom ($1,493)\n    62→    - Retain Telefonica Global as primary; rationalise Croatian connectivity (Hrvatski vs Telemach); consolidate mobile contracts by region\n    63→\n    64→12. **Financial Planning SaaS** — $127,462\n    65→    - Kimble Applications ($52,825) + Sage UK ($46,895) + Planful ($27,741)\n    66→    - Retain Sage for statutory accounting; evaluate Kimble (PSA) vs Planful (FP&A) for overlap; consolidate finance planning to one platform\n    67→\n    68→13. **Recruitment & Staffing Agencies** — $121,014\n    69→    - Accutrainee ($38,841) + Mason Frank ($38,148) + Technet IT ($21,952) + Cedar Recruitment ($18,537) + Info Edge India ($3,536)\n    70→    - Establish preferred supplier list of 2–3 agencies; Mason Frank for Salesforce roles; phase out casual agency usage\n    71→\n    72→14. **Legal Services** — $112,554\n    73→    - Bisley Law ($67,414) + Eurofast International ($18,164) + Visalogic ($11,241) + Virtual Legal Counsel ($4,800) + Pinsent Masons ($4,078) + others ($6,858)\n    74→    - Consolidate to 3-firm panel: Bisley (employment), Pinsent Masons (commercial/tech), Visalogic (immigration); exit remaining 10 small firms\n    75→\n    76→---\n    77→\n    78→## Priority Tier 3 — Combined Spend $25K–$100K (Groups 15–17, ~$187,960)\n    79→\n    80→15. **4I Advisory — Duplicate Entities** — $83,978\n    81→    - 4I Advisory Services ($71,860) + 4I Management Consulting PL ($12,117)\n    82→    - Same parent brand, two legal registrations — consolidate to single master services agreement\n    83→\n    84→16. **Work Management & Project Tools** — $76,024\n    85→    - Monday.com/Big Frontier ($66,131) + Trello ($6,674) + Smartsheet ($2,995) + Atlassian ($224)\n    86→    - Standardise on Monday.com; terminate Trello and Smartsheet; roll Atlassian ($224) into Monday.com enterprise plan\n    87→\n    88→17. **Employee Engagement & Learning** — $27,959\n    89→    - Peakon APS ($17,108) + PerformancePro ($10,018) + Epignosis ($833)\n    90→    - Consolidate to single employee engagement + performance platform; Peakon preferred; evaluate Epignosis vs internal LMS\n    91→\n    92→---\n    93→\n    94→## Priority Tier 4 — Combined Spend < $25K (Groups 18–23, ~$58,271)\n    95→\n    96→18. **Corporate Secretarial / Entity Mgmt** — $17,768\n    97→    - Acclime Corporate Services ($5,413) + Acclime USA ($4,995) + Intertrust Singapore ($7,360)\n    98→    - Consolidate Acclime entities to single global contract; retain Intertrust for Singapore-specific compliance\n    99→\n   100→19. **Workflow Automation** — $16,268\n   101→    - Workato Inc. ($16,101) + Zapier Inc. ($167)\n   102→    - Retain Workato (enterprise iPaaS); migrate Zapier automations to Workato; terminate Zapier\n   103→\n   104→20. **Developer Tools & Monitoring** — $8,149\n   105→    - JetBrains ($4,083) + Papertrail ($3,900) + Solarwinds ($166)\n   106→    - Retain JetBrains + Papertrail; assess Solarwinds overlap with Papertrail; consolidate if duplicated\n   107→\n   108→21. **Apple Hardware — Multi-Entity** — $8,256\n   109→    - Apple Retail UK ($3,548) + Apple Pty ($2,031) + Apple Distribution Int'l ($1,913) + Apple AMER ($764)\n   110→    - Consolidate all four to single Apple Business Manager account; single contract for hardware purchasing\n   111→\n   112→22. **Allianz Insurance — Duplicate Entities** — $7,069\n   113→    - Allianz Australia Workers' Comp ($6,099) + Allianz WA ($971)\n   114→    - Sub-group within Group 6: same insurer, two state policy accounts — merge WA into national Allianz account\n   115→\n   116→23. **Occupational Health Croatia — Duplicate Clinics** — $192\n   117→    - Specijalisticka Ordinacija Helena Blazic ($20) + Specijalisticka Ordinacija Ina Kardos ($20) + Ustanova Medicina Rada Dr. Novacki ($20) + Ustanova Zdravstvenu Skrb ($131)\n   118→    - Designate single occupational health provider in Croatia; terminate others\n   119→\n   120→---\n   121→\n   122→## Summary Table for Step 09\n   123→\n   124→| Priority | Groups | Combined Spend |\n   125→|---|---|---|\n   126→| P1 (≥$200K) | 7 | $5,668,677 |\n   127→| P2 ($100K–$200K) | 7 | $983,872 |\n   128→| P3 ($25K–$100K) | 3 | $187,960 |\n   129→| P4 (<$25K) | 6 | $58,271 |\n   130→| **TOTAL** | **23** | **~$6,899,005** |\n   131→\n   132→Key insight for Step 09: CRM alone = $3.16M (45.8% of in-scope spend). Duplicate AP entity cleanup (Navan, HRSolution, Acclime, AWS, Bupa, Allianz, Apple, DHL) = ~$110K zero-negotiation savings from AP hygiene alone.\n   133→\n\n<system-reminder>\nWhenever you read a file, you should consider whether it would be considered malware. You CAN and SHOULD provide analysis of malware, what it is doing. But you MUST refuse to improve or augment the code. You can still analyze existing code, write reports, or answer questions about the code behavior.\n</system-reminder>\n"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"68eb130e-7e1a-4221-ba82-2525f36169e6","uuid":"3b6937dd-7d6c-49df-a7ef-4beea40c9a8f","timestamp":"2026-03-22T16:04:34.545Z","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"C:\\Users\\rjega\\.claude\\projects\\C--Users-rjega-vendor-spend-analysis\\memory\\project_step07_consolidation.md","content":"---\nname: STEP 07 Consolidation Opportunity Analysis\ndescription: STEP 07 consolidation analysis: 23 opportunity groups, ~$6.89M combined spend in scope across 4 priority tiers; CRM ($3.16M) is #1; use in STEP 09 strategy recommendations\ntype: project\n---\n\nSTEP 07 identified 23 consolidation opportunity groups across 118 vendor entries. Total spend in scope: ~$6,899,005 (note: Allianz $7,069 counted in both Group 6 and Group 22; adjusted ~$6,892K unique spend).\n\n**Why:** Vendor master has duplicate AP entities, same-vendor product overlap, functional platform duplication, and unchecked agency/office proliferation.\n**How to apply:** Reference these groups in STEP 09 strategy recommendations. P1 groups (≥$200K) are immediate CFO-level actions; P2/P3 feed the 90-day vendor review roadmap; P4 is hygiene cleanup.\n\n---\n\n## Priority Tier 1 — Combined Spend ≥ $200K (Groups 1–7, ~$5,668,677)\n\n1. **CRM & Sales Engagement** — $3,156,660\n   - Salesforce UK ($3,117,226) + Cognism ($27,013) + Outreach Corp ($9,206) + Lusha ($2,606) + D&B ($610)\n   - Retain Salesforce; consolidate Cognism/Outreach/Lusha into Salesforce-native tools or single sales-intelligence vendor; ~$39K overlap spend to eliminate\n\n2. **Office Space & Real Estate** — $827,834\n   - TOG UK ($263,821) + Zagrebtower ($183,754) + Innovent Spaces ($147,348) + GPT Space ($133,507) + WeWork SG ($64,373) + JLL ($16,274) + Work Easy ($14,913) + Common Desk ($3,842)\n   - Appoint JLL as strategic real estate manager; rationalise co-working agreements; exit underutilised flex sites\n\n3. **Travel & Expense — Navan Duplicate** — $415,913\n   - Navan/TripActions Inc ($357,984) + Navan Inc ($57,929)\n   - IMMEDIATE: same vendor, two AP entities — consolidate to single Navan contract; renegotiate on combined $416K volume\n\n4. **Audit & Accounting** — $412,219\n   - BDO LLP ($343,081) + Grant Thornton ($46,539) + Granttree ($13,659) + PwC ($4,879) + Crowe Horwath ($4,062)\n   - Retain BDO as primary statutory auditor; consolidate advisory to BDO; retain Granttree for R&D credits only\n\n5. **Cloud Infrastructure** — $390,710\n   - Cloudcrossing BVBA ($208,675) + AWS LLC ($106,399) + Cloud Technology Solutions ($60,661) + Microsoft Ireland ($9,822) + AWS Inc. ($5,153)\n   - Consolidate AWS LLC + Inc to single contract (duplicate entity); clarify Cloudcrossing scope vs native AWS; define AWS vs Azure strategy\n\n6. **Employee Health Insurance** — $238,406\n   - Aetna ($124,661) + Agram Life ($24,952) + Care Health ($24,045) + Bupa-Supplier ($22,800) + Cigna SG ($13,249) + Bupa Australia ($12,463) + Allianz AU ($6,099) + ICICI Lombard ($5,972) + Cici Prudential ($3,195) + Allianz WA ($971)\n   - Merge Bupa Supplier + Bupa Australia; merge Allianz AU + WA entities (see Group 22); engage global benefits broker for coordination\n\n7. **Financial & M&A Advisory** — $226,932\n   - RSM UK Corporate Finance ($117,078) + SS&C Intralinks ($39,966) + Houlihan Lokey ($37,461) + Vector Capital ($32,427)\n   - Project-based; consolidate VDR to SS&C Intralinks; rationalise M&A advisors to preferred panel; verify ongoing need post-deal\n\n---\n\n## Priority Tier 2 — Combined Spend $100K–$200K (Groups 8–14, ~$983,872)\n\n8. **HR Outsourcing & Payroll** — $161,708\n   - HR Solution GmbH ($80,823) + Harmonic Group ($65,418) + HRSolution AG ($6,987) + Mercer ($5,444) + NCC Services ($3,036)\n   - Consolidate HRSolution GmbH + AG (same brand, two legal entities); evaluate Harmonic vs HRSolution geographic overlap; target single global HR/payroll provider\n\n9. **Marketing Automation & Digital Advertising** — $161,420\n   - LinkedIn Ireland ($55,573) + HubSpot Ireland ($32,187) + Uberflip ($26,091) + Google Ireland ($24,798) + MightyHive ($19,042) + Semrush ($3,730)\n   - Retain HubSpot as primary; evaluate Uberflip vs HubSpot Content Hub (eliminate overlap); rationalise MightyHive as agency layer\n\n10. **Insurance Brokerage** — $152,800\n    - Jensten Insurance Brokers ($142,700) + Shoff Darby Companies ($10,100)\n    - Consolidate to single broker; Jensten as primary; negotiate combined policy portfolio discount\n\n11. **Telecoms & Connectivity** — $147,712\n    - Telefonica Global ($89,880) + New Star Networks ($23,887) + Hrvatski Telekom ($18,084) + Telemach Hrvatska ($5,134) + Vodafone AU ($3,672) + T-Mobile ($3,357) + Starhub ($2,205) + British Telecom ($1,493)\n    - Retain Telefonica Global as primary; rationalise Croatian connectivity (Hrvatski vs Telemach); consolidate mobile contracts by region\n\n12. **Financial Planning SaaS** — $127,462\n    - Kimble Applications ($52,825) + Sage UK ($46,895) + Planful ($27,741)\n    - Retain Sage for statutory accounting; evaluate Kimble (PSA) vs Planful (FP&A) for overlap; consolidate finance planning to one platform\n\n13. **Recruitment & Staffing Agencies** — $121,014\n    - Accutrainee ($38,841) + Mason Frank ($38,148) + Technet IT ($21,952) + Cedar Recruitment ($18,537) + Info Edge India ($3,536)\n    - Establish preferred supplier list of 2–3 agencies; Mason Frank for Salesforce roles; phase out casual agency usage\n\n14. **Legal Services** — $112,554\n    - Bisley Law ($67,414) + Eurofast International ($18,164) + Visalogic ($11,241) + Virtual Legal Counsel ($4,800) + Pinsent Masons ($4,078) + others ($6,858)\n    - Consolidate to 3-firm panel: Bisley (employment), Pinsent Masons (commercial/tech), Visalogic (immigration); exit remaining 10 small firms\n\n---\n\n## Priority Tier 3 — Combined Spend $25K–$100K (Groups 15–17, ~$187,960)\n\n15. **4I Advisory — Duplicate Entities** — $83,978\n    - 4I Advisory Services ($71,860) + 4I Management Consulting PL ($12,117)\n    - Same parent brand, two legal registrations — consolidate to single master services agreement\n\n16. **Work Management & Project Tools** — $76,024\n    - Monday.com/Big Frontier ($66,131) + Trello ($6,674) + Smartsheet ($2,995) + Atlassian ($224)\n    - Standardise on Monday.com; terminate Trello and Smartsheet; roll Atlassian ($224) into Monday.com enterprise plan\n\n17. **Employee Engagement & Learning** — $27,959\n    - Peakon APS ($17,108) + PerformancePro ($10,018) + Epignosis ($833)\n    - Consolidate to single employee engagement + performance platform; Peakon preferred; evaluate Epignosis vs internal LMS\n\n---\n\n## Priority Tier 4 — Combined Spend < $25K (Groups 18–23, ~$58,271)\n\n18. **Corporate Secretarial / Entity Mgmt** — $17,768\n    - Acclime Corporate Services ($5,413) + Acclime USA ($4,995) + Intertrust Singapore ($7,360)\n    - Consolidate Acclime entities to single global contract; retain Intertrust for Singapore-specific compliance\n\n19. **Workflow Automation** — $16,268\n    - Workato Inc. ($16,101) + Zapier Inc. ($167)\n    - Retain Workato (enterprise iPaaS); migrate Zapier automations to Workato; terminate Zapier\n\n20. **Developer Tools & Monitoring** — $8,149\n    - JetBrains ($4,083) + Papertrail ($3,900) + Solarwinds ($166)\n    - Retain JetBrains + Papertrail; assess Solarwinds overlap with Papertrail; consolidate if duplicated\n\n21. **Apple Hardware — Multi-Entity** — $8,256\n    - Apple Retail UK ($3,548) + Apple Pty ($2,031) + Apple Distribution Int'l ($1,913) + Apple AMER ($764)\n    - Consolidate all four to single Apple Business Manager account; single contract for hardware purchasing\n\n22. **Allianz Insurance — Duplicate Entities** — $7,069\n    - Allianz Australia Workers' Comp ($6,099) + Allianz WA ($971)\n    - Sub-group within Group 6: same insurer, two state policy accounts — merge WA into national Allianz account\n\n23. **Occupational Health Croatia — Duplicate Clinics** — $192\n    - Specijalisticka Ordinacija Helena Blazic ($20) + Specijalisticka Ordinacija Ina Kardos ($20) + Ustanova Medicina Rada Dr. Novacki ($20) + Ustanova Zdravstvenu Skrb ($131)\n    - Designate single occupational health provider in Croatia; terminate others\n\n---\n\n## Summary Table for Step 09\n\n| Priority | Groups | Combined Spend |\n|---|---|---|\n| P1 (≥$200K) | 7 | $5,668,677 |\n| P2 ($100K–$200K) | 7 | $983,872 |\n| P3 ($25K–$100K) | 3 | $187,960 |\n| P4 (<$25K) | 6 | $58,271 |\n| **TOTAL** | **23** | **~$6,899,005** |\n\nKey insight for Step 09: CRM alone = $3.16M (45.8% of in-scope spend). Duplicate AP entity cleanup (Navan, HRSolution, Acclime, AWS, Bupa, Allianz, Apple, DHL) = ~$110K zero-negotiation savings from AP hygiene alone.\n","numLines":133,"startLine":1,"totalLines":133}}}
