nsolidate)","+- Navan, Inc: $57,929 (Optimize → Consolidate — duplicate AP entity, not strategic in own right)","+","+## Trade-off Parameters Applied","+","+| Score | Switching Cost | Implementation Effort | Time to Realise |","+|-------|---------------|----------------------|-----------------|","+| 5 | HIGH | HIGH | LONG |","+| 4 | HIGH | HIGH | LONG |","+| 3 | MEDIUM | MEDIUM | MEDIUM |","+| 2 | LOW | LOW | IMMEDIATE–MEDIUM |","+| 1 | LOW | LOW | IMMEDIATE |","+","+Time to Realise also driven by recommendation:","+- Terminate → IMMEDIATE (0–3 months)","+- Consolidate → MEDIUM (3–6 months)","+- Optimize → LONG (6–12 months)","+"," ## Key Conflict Tiers for Step 09"," ","-### Tier A — Score 4 Consolidate → Optimize (9 vendors): HIGH PRIORITY","-Vendors with significant switching cost being under-classified. Recommend upgrading all 9.","+### Tier A — Score 4 mis-classified as Consolidate/Terminate (10 vendors): HIGH PRIORITY","+Upgrade to Optimize: Jensten, RSM UK, Telefonica, HR Solution GmbH, 4I Advisory, Infosys, Big Frontier, Harmonic, WeWork SG, TMForum"," ","-### Tier B — Score 3 Terminate → Consolidate (11 vendors): MEDIUM PRIORITY","-Key: Amazon Web Services Inc. (separate entity, Engineering), Sage UK (Finance software),","-Grant Thornton (advisory), SS&C Intralinks (M&A data room), Vector Capital (M&A advisory),","-Croatian telecom: Hrvatski Telekom, Telemach Hrvatska, New Star Networks.","+### Tier B — Score 3 mis-classified as Terminate (3 vendors): MEDIUM PRIORITY","+Upgrade to Consolidate: Innovent Spaces ($147K), Weking D.O.O. ($144K), GPT Space ($133K) — all are active co-working/facilities vendors"," ","-### Tier C — Score 2 Terminate → Consolidate (167 vendors): SYSTEMATIC FINDING","-Over-termination pattern: 167 Score-2 vendors terminated without consolidation evaluation.","-Many are insurance, SaaS tools, local professional services — marginal but non-zero value.","-Step 09 should flag this as a governance gap (no preferred-supplier program in place).","+### Tier C — Score 2/1 over-termination (105 vendors): GOVERNANCE FINDING","+118 total conflicts; bulk are low-spend vendors where Terminate is applied without consolidation evaluation. Flag as portfolio governance gap in Step 09."," "," ## Step 09 Use"," ","-1. Upgrade 9 Consolidate→Optimize vendors (Tier A) in final recommendation","+1. Upgrade 10 Consolidate/Terminate→Optimize vendors (Tier A) in final recommendation"," 2. Salesforce + AWS = Score 5 confirmed; anchor Step 09 strategy around protecting these","-3. 187 conflicts = 48% misalignment — cite as portfolio governance issue in strategy memo","-4. Tier B telecom/audit consolidation = quick win for cost reduction narrative","+3. 118 conflicts = 31% misalignment — cite as portfolio governance issue in strategy memo","+4. Tier B co-working facilities ($424K combined) = consolidation quick win"]}],"originalFile":"---\nname: STEP 08 Strategic Scores\ndescription: Strategic scores (1–5) for all 386 vendors, 187 conflicts flagged; 9 Score-4 vendors need Consolidate→Optimize upgrade; use in STEP 09\ntype: project\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n- **Total vendors scored:** 386\n- **Total conflicts (current rec ≠ score-aligned rec):** 187\n- **Output file:** `C:/Users/rjega/vendor-spend-analysis/outputs/step08_strategic_scores.csv`\n\n## Score Distribution\n\n| Score | Label | Count |\n|-------|-------|-------|\n| 5 | Mission critical, cannot be replaced | 2 |\n| 4 | Strategic, significant switching cost | 13 |\n| 3 | Important but substitutable | 22 |\n| 2 | Marginal value, overlap exists | 167 |\n| 1 | Redundant or low-value | 182 |\n\n## Score 5 — Mission Critical (2 vendors)\n\n| Vendor | Dept | Spend | Current Rec |\n|--------|------|-------|-------------|\n| Salesforce UK Ltd | Engineering | $3,117,226 | Optimize ✅ |\n| Amazon Web Services Llc | Engineering | $106,399 | Optimize ✅ |\n\n## Score 4 — Strategic (13 vendors)\n\n| Vendor | Spend | Current Rec | Aligned | Conflict |\n|--------|-------|-------------|---------|----------|\n| Cloudcrossing Bvba | $208,675 | Optimize | Optimize | N |\n| Bdo Llp | $343,081 | Optimize | Optimize | N |\n| Tog Uk Properties Ltd | $263,821 | Optimize | Optimize | N |\n| Aetna Life And Casualty Ltd | $124,661 | Consolidate | Optimize | Y |\n| Zagrebtower D.O.O. | ~$83K | Consolidate | Optimize | Y |\n| Weking D.O.O. | ~$70K | Consolidate | Optimize | Y |\n| Gpt Space & Co | ~$65K | Consolidate | Optimize | Y |\n| Big Frontier Pty Ltd (Cult Of Monday) | $66,131 | Consolidate | Optimize | Y |\n| Bisley Law Ltd | $67,414 | Consolidate | Optimize | Y |\n| Cloud Technology Solutions Ltd | $60,661 | Consolidate | Optimize | Y |\n| Wework Singapore Pte. Ltd. | ~$50K | Consolidate | Optimize | Y |\n| Tmforum | ~$50K | Consolidate | Optimize | Y |\n| Hr Solution International Pte. Ltd. | ~$50K | Consolidate | Optimize | Y |\n\n**9 of 13 Score-4 vendors are currently \"Consolidate\" but should be \"Optimize\"**\n\n## Key Conflict Tiers for Step 09\n\n### Tier A — Score 4 Consolidate → Optimize (9 vendors): HIGH PRIORITY\nVendors with significant switching cost being under-classified. Recommend upgrading all 9.\n\n### Tier B — Score 3 Terminate → Consolidate (11 vendors): MEDIUM PRIORITY\nKey: Amazon Web Services Inc. (separate entity, Engineering), Sage UK (Finance software),\nGrant Thornton (advisory), SS&C Intralinks (M&A data room), Vector Capital (M&A advisory),\nCroatian telecom: Hrvatski Telekom, Telemach Hrvatska, New Star Networks.\n\n### Tier C — Score 2 Terminate → Consolidate (167 vendors): SYSTEMATIC FINDING\nOver-termination pattern: 167 Score-2 vendors terminated without consolidation evaluation.\nMany are insurance, SaaS tools, local professional services — marginal but non-zero value.\nStep 09 should flag this as a governance gap (no preferred-supplier program in place).\n\n## Step 09 Use\n\n1. Upgrade 9 Consolidate→Optimize vendors (Tier A) in final recommendation\n2. Salesforce + AWS = Score 5 confirmed; anchor Step 09 strategy around protecting these\n3. 187 conflicts = 48% misalignment — cite as portfolio governance issue in strategy memo\n4. Tier B telecom/audit consolidation = quick win for cost reduction narrative\n"}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01G1XJHkgEMypy7dAqDTCuLL","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"---\n\n## STEP 08 — Strategic Scoring & Trade-off Analysis\n\n**386 vendors scored | 118 conflicts flagged | Output written to `STEP08 Strategic Scores` sheet + CSV**\n\n---\n\n### Score Distribution\n\n| Score | Label | Count | Logic |\n|-------|-------|-------|-------|\n| 5 | Mission Critical | 2 | Cannot be replaced; single-source dependency |\n| 4 | Strategic | 18 | High switching cost; embedded in operations |\n| 3 | Important | 13 | Substitutable with moderate effort |\n| 2 | Marginal | 58 | Low value; overlap exists; Consolidate candidates |\n| 1 | Redundant | 295 | One-off, tail spend, or clearly unnecessary |\n\n---\n\n### STEP 4 — Structured Output Table (Top Vendors by Spend)\n\n| Vendor Name | Score | Suggestion | Switching Cost | Effort | Time | Conflict |\n|-------------|-------|------------|----------------|--------|------|----------|\n| Salesforce Uk Ltd-Uk | **5** | Optimize | HIGH | HIGH | LONG | **N** |\n| Navan (Tripactions Inc) | **4** | Optimize | HIGH | HIGH | LONG | **N** |\n| Bdo Llp | **4** | Optimize | HIGH | HIGH | LONG | **N** |\n| Tog Uk Properties Limited | **4** | Optimize | HIGH | HIGH | LONG | **N** |\n| Cloudcrossing Bvba | **4** | Optimize | HIGH | HIGH | LONG | **N** |\n| Zagrebtower D.O.O. | **4** | Optimize | HIGH | HIGH | LONG | **N** |\n| Innovent Spaces Private Limited | **3** | ~~Terminate~~ → Consolidate | MEDIUM | MEDIUM | MEDIUM | **Y** |\n| Weking D.O.O. | **3** | ~~Terminate~~ → Consolidate | MEDIUM | MEDIUM | MEDIUM | **Y** |\n| Jensten Insurance Brokers | **4** | ~~Consolidate~~ → Optimize | HIGH | HIGH | LONG | **Y** |\n| Gpt Space & Co | **3** | ~~Terminate~~ → Consolidate | MEDIUM | MEDIUM | MEDIUM | **Y** |\n| Aetna Life And Casualty Ltd | **4** | Optimize | HIGH | HIGH | LONG | **N** |\n| Rsm Uk Corporate Finance Llp | **4** | ~~Consolidate~~ → Optimize | HIGH | HIGH | LONG | **Y** |\n| Amazon Web Services Llc | **5** | Optimize | HIGH | HIGH | LONG | **N** |\n| Telefonica Global Services Gmbh | **4** | ~~Consolidate~~ → Optimize | HIGH | HIGH | LONG | **Y** |\n| Hr Solution International Gmbh | **4** | ~~Consolidate~~ → Optimize | HIGH | HIGH | LONG | **Y** |\n| 4I Advisory Services | **4** | ~~Consolidate~~ → Optimize | HIGH | HIGH | LONG | **Y** |\n| Bisley Law Ltd | **4** | Optimize | HIGH | HIGH | LONG | **N** |\n| Infosys | **4** | ~~Consolidate~~ → Optimize | HIGH | HIGH | LONG | **Y** |\n| Big Frontier Pty Ltd (Cult Of Monday) | **4** | ~~Consolidate~~ → Optimize | HIGH | HIGH | LONG | **Y** |\n| Harmonic Group Limited | **4** | ~~Consolidate~~ → Optimize | HIGH | HIGH | LONG | **Y** |\n| Wework Singapore Pte. Ltd. | **4** | ~~Terminate~~ → Optimize | HIGH | HIGH | LONG | **Y** |\n| Cloud Technology Solutions Ltd | **4** | ~~Consolidate~~ → Optimize | HIGH | HIGH | LONG | **Y** |\n| Navan, Inc | **3** | ~~Optimize~~ → Consolidate | MEDIUM | MEDIUM | MEDIUM | **Y** |\n| Tmforum | **4** | ~~Terminate~~ → Optimize | HIGH | HIGH | LONG | **Y** |\n| Linkedin Ireland Limited | **3** | Consolidate | MEDIUM | MEDIUM | MEDIUM | **N** |\n| Kimble Applications Ltd | **3** | Consolidate | MEDIUM | MEDIUM | MEDIUM | **N** |\n| Sage Uk Limited | **3** | Consolidate | MEDIUM | MEDIUM | MEDIUM | **N** |\n| Grant Thornton | **3** | Consolidate | MEDIUM | MEDIUM | MEDIUM | **N** |\n| Ss&C Intralinks Inc | **3** | Consolidate | MEDIUM | MEDIUM | MEDIUM | **N** |\n| *(295 Score-1 vendors)* | **1** | Terminate | LOW | LOW | IMMEDIATE | N |\n\n---\n\n### Conflict Summary — 118 Total\n\n| Conflict Type | Count | Combined Spend | Priority |\n|---------------|-------|----------------|----------|\n| Score 4 → mis-classified Consolidate/Terminate | 10 | ~$870K | HIGH |\n| Score 3 → mis-classified Terminate | 3 | ~$425K | MEDIUM |\n| Score 1/2 → minor mis-classification | 105 | ~$1.1M tail | GOVERNANCE |\n\n---\n\n### Key Trade-off Findings for STEP 09\n\n**1. Score 4 upgrades (10 vendors, ~$870K combined spend)**\nThese vendors have HIGH switching cost and are embedded in operations — being classified Consolidate/Terminate understates their risk and overstates ease of exit. All 10 should be reclassified to **Optimize** before STEP 09 strategy is finalised.\n\n**2. Score 3 co-working facilities (3 vendors, ~$425K)**\nInnovent Spaces, Weking, and GPT Space are all active office/flex space providers marked **Terminate**. Given MEDIUM switching cost and active occupancy, these should be **Consolidate** (rationalise to preferred operator, not immediate exit).\n\n**3. Navan, Inc — Score 3, Optimize → Consolidate (conflict)**\nThis is the duplicate AP entity for Navan/TripActions ($57,929). It should be Consolidate (merge into primary Navan contract), not Optimize as a standalone. One of the clearest process fixes.\n\n**4. 118 conflicts = 31% of portfolio misaligned**\nSignals no formal strategic scoring framework existed before this exercise. Step 09 should recommend implementing a vendor tiering policy to prevent future misclassification.\n\n---\n\nResults stored in:\n- `outputs/step08_strategic_scores.csv` — full 386-row scored dataset\n- `STEP08 Strategic Scores` sheet — formatted table in main workbook\n- Memory updated for STEP 09 use"}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1888,"cache_read_input_tokens":33466,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1888,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"68eb130e-7e1a-4221-ba82-2525f36169e6","uuid":"dfc63a01-dc6c-4728-9628-f78ed6e86ded"}
