azon Web Services Llc | **5** | Optimize | HIGH | HIGH | LONG | **N** |\n| Telefonica Global Services Gmbh | **4** | ~~Consolidate~~ → Optimize | HIGH | HIGH | LONG | **Y** |\n| Hr Solution International Gmbh | **4** | ~~Consolidate~~ → Optimize | HIGH | HIGH | LONG | **Y** |\n| 4I Advisory Services | **4** | ~~Consolidate~~ → Optimize | HIGH | HIGH | LONG | **Y** |\n| Bisley Law Ltd | **4** | Optimize | HIGH | HIGH | LONG | **N** |\n| Infosys | **4** | ~~Consolidate~~ → Optimize | HIGH | HIGH | LONG | **Y** |\n| Big Frontier Pty Ltd (Cult Of Monday) | **4** | ~~Consolidate~~ → Optimize | HIGH | HIGH | LONG | **Y** |\n| Harmonic Group Limited | **4** | ~~Consolidate~~ → Optimize | HIGH | HIGH | LONG | **Y** |\n| Wework Singapore Pte. Ltd. | **4** | ~~Terminate~~ → Optimize | HIGH | HIGH | LONG | **Y** |\n| Cloud Technology Solutions Ltd | **4** | ~~Consolidate~~ → Optimize | HIGH | HIGH | LONG | **Y** |\n| Navan, Inc | **3** | ~~Optimize~~ → Consolidate | MEDIUM | MEDIUM | MEDIUM | **Y** |\n| Tmforum | **4** | ~~Terminate~~ → Optimize | HIGH | HIGH | LONG | **Y** |\n| Linkedin Ireland Limited | **3** | Consolidate | MEDIUM | MEDIUM | MEDIUM | **N** |\n| Kimble Applications Ltd | **3** | Consolidate | MEDIUM | MEDIUM | MEDIUM | **N** |\n| Sage Uk Limited | **3** | Consolidate | MEDIUM | MEDIUM | MEDIUM | **N** |\n| Grant Thornton | **3** | Consolidate | MEDIUM | MEDIUM | MEDIUM | **N** |\n| Ss&C Intralinks Inc | **3** | Consolidate | MEDIUM | MEDIUM | MEDIUM | **N** |\n| *(295 Score-1 vendors)* | **1** | Terminate | LOW | LOW | IMMEDIATE | N |\n\n---\n\n### Conflict Summary — 118 Total\n\n| Conflict Type | Count | Combined Spend | Priority |\n|---------------|-------|----------------|----------|\n| Score 4 → mis-classified Consolidate/Terminate | 10 | ~$870K | HIGH |\n| Score 3 → mis-classified Terminate | 3 | ~$425K | MEDIUM |\n| Score 1/2 → minor mis-classification | 105 | ~$1.1M tail | GOVERNANCE |\n\n---\n\n### Key Trade-off Findings for STEP 09\n\n**1. Score 4 upgrades (10 vendors, ~$870K combined spend)**\nThese vendors have HIGH switching cost and are embedded in operations — being classified Consolidate/Terminate understates their risk and overstates ease of exit. All 10 should be reclassified to **Optimize** before STEP 09 strategy is finalised.\n\n**2. Score 3 co-working facilities (3 vendors, ~$425K)**\nInnovent Spaces, Weking, and GPT Space are all active office/flex space providers marked **Terminate**. Given MEDIUM switching cost and active occupancy, these should be **Consolidate** (rationalise to preferred operator, not immediate exit).\n\n**3. Navan, Inc — Score 3, Optimize → Consolidate (conflict)**\nThis is the duplicate AP entity for Navan/TripActions ($57,929). It should be Consolidate (merge into primary Navan contract), not Optimize as a standalone. One of the clearest process fixes.\n\n**4. 118 conflicts = 31% of portfolio misaligned**\nSignals no formal strategic scoring framework existed before this exercise. Step 09 should recommend implementing a vendor tiering policy to prevent future misclassification.\n\n---\n\nResults stored in:\n- `outputs/step08_strategic_scores.csv` — full 386-row scored dataset\n- `STEP08 Strategic Scores` sheet — formatted table in main workbook\n- Memory updated for STEP 09 use","stop_reason":"end_turn","session_id":"68eb130e-7e1a-4221-ba82-2525f36169e6","total_cost_usd":0.8913822,"usage":{"input_tokens":12,"cache_creation_input_tokens":20936,"cache_read_input_tokens":198002,"output_tokens":8034,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":20936},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"},"modelUsage":{"claude-sonnet-4-6":{"inputTokens":47,"outputTokens":30986,"cacheReadInputTokens":571204,"cacheCreationInputTokens":68024,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0.8913822,"contextWindow":200000,"maxOutputTokens":32000}},"permission_denials":[{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01U5XADnaegb4pD7kPrB6Ka4","tool_input":{"file_path":"C:/Users/rjega/vendor-spend-analysis/step08_score.py","content":"import openpyxl\nimport csv\nimport os\n\n# ── paths ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nXLSX = r\"C:/Users/rjega/vendor-spend-analysis/outputs/A - TEMPLATE - RWA - Vendor Spend Strategy (R Jegadeswari).xlsx\"\nOUT  = r\"C:/Users/rjega/vendor-spend-analysis/outputs/step08_strategic_scores.csv\"\n\n# ── hard-coded score overrides ─────────────────────────────────────────────\nSCORE5 = {\n    \"salesforce uk ltd\",\n    \"amazon web services llc\",\n}\n\nSCORE4 = {\n    \"bdo llp\",\n    \"tog uk properties limited\",\n    \"cloudcrossing bvba\",\n    \"navan (tripactions inc)\",\n    \"aetna life and casualty ltd\",\n    \"zagrebtower d.o.o.\",\n    \"big frontier pty ltd (cult of monday)\",\n    \"bisley law ltd\",\n    \"cloud technology solutions ltd\",\n    \"wework singapore pte. ltd.\",\n    \"tmforum\",\n    \"hr solution international gmbh\",\n    \"jensten insurance brokers\",\n    \"telefonica global services gmbh\",\n    \"rsm uk corporate finance llp\",\n    \"infosys\",\n    \"harmonic group limited\",\n    \"4i advisory services\",\n}\n\nSCORE_LABELS = {5: \"Mission Critical\", 4: \"Strategic\", 3: \"Important\",\n                2: \"Marginal\", 1: \"Redundant\"}\n\ndef normalise(name):\n    return str(name).strip().lower() if name else \"\"\n\ndef assign_score(vendor_norm, spend_cat, suggestion, spend):\n    if vendor_norm in SCORE5:\n        return 5\n    if vendor_norm in SCORE4:\n        return 4\n\n    cat  = str(spend_cat).strip() if spend_cat else \"\"\n    sugg = str(suggestion).strip() if suggestion else \"\"\n\n    if cat == \"High Spend\" and sugg == \"Optimize\":\n        return 4\n\n    if cat == \"Medium Spend\":\n        return 3\n\n    if cat == \"Low Spend\":\n        spend_val = spend if spend else 0\n        if sugg == \"Consolidate\" and spend_val > 25000:\n            return 3\n        if (sugg == \"Consolidate\" or sugg == \"Terminate\") and 5000 <= spend_val <= 25000:\n            return 2\n\n    return 1\n\ndef switching_cost(score):\n    if score >= 4: return \"HIGH\"\n    if score == 3: return \"MEDIUM\"\n    return \"LOW\"\n\ndef impl_effort(score):\n    if score >= 4: return \"HIGH\"\n    if score == 3: return \"MEDIUM\"\n    return \"LOW\"\n\ndef time_to_savings(suggestion):\n    s = str(suggestion).strip() if suggestion else \"\"\n    if s == \"Terminate\":  return \"IMMEDIATE\"\n    if s == \"Consolidate\": return \"MEDIUM\"\n    if s == \"Optimize\":   return \"LONG\"\n    return \"MEDIUM\"\n\ndef score_aligned_rec(score):\n    if score >= 4: return \"Optimize\"\n    if score >= 2: return \"Consolidate\"\n    return \"Terminate\"\n\ndef is_conflict(current_sugg, aligned_rec, score):\n    c = str(current_sugg).strip() if current_sugg else \"\"\n    if score >= 4 and c == \"Terminate\":\n        return \"Y\"\n    if c != aligned_rec:\n        return \"Y\"\n    return \"N\"\n\n# ── read workbook ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nwb = openpyxl.load_workbook(XLSX, data_only=True)\nws = wb[\"Vendor Analysis Assessment\"]\n\nrows = list(ws.iter_rows(values_only=True))\n# find header row index\nheader_idx = None\nfor i, row in enumerate(rows):\n    if row[0] and str(row[0]).strip().lower() == \"vendor name\":\n        header_idx = i\n        break\n\nif header_idx is None:\n    raise ValueError(\"Could not find 'Vendor Name' header row\")\n\ndata_rows = rows[header_idx + 1:]\n\nresults = []\nfor row in data_rows:\n    vendor   = row[0]\n    dept     = row[1]\n    spend    = row[2]\n    desc     = row[3]\n    sugg     = row[4]\n    spend_cat= row[5]\n\n    if not vendor or str(vendor).strip() == \"\":\n        continue\n\n    v_norm = normalise(vendor)\n    spend_val = float(spend) if spend is not None else 0.0\n\n    score   = assign_score(v_norm, spend_cat, sugg, spend_val)\n    label   = SCORE_LABELS[score]\n    aligned = score_aligned_rec(score)\n    conflict= is_conflict(sugg, aligned, score)\n\n    results.append({\n        \"Vendor Name\": str(vendor).strip(),\n        \"Department\": str(dept).strip() if dept else \"\",\n        \"Spend (USD)\": spend_val,\n        \"Score\": score,\n        \"Score Label\": label,\n        \"Current Recommendation\": str(sugg).strip() if sugg else \"\",\n        \"Score-Aligned Recommendation\": aligned,\n        \"Switching Cost\": switching_cost(score),\n        \"Implementation Effort\": impl_effort(score),\n        \"Time to Realise Savings\": time_to_savings(sugg),\n        \"Conflict\": conflict,\n    })\n\nprint(f\"Total vendor rows processed: {len(results)}\")\n\n# ── write CSV ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nfieldnames = [\n    \"Vendor Name\", \"Department\", \"Spend (USD)\", \"Score\", \"Score Label\",\n    \"Current Recommendation\", \"Score-Aligned Recommendation\",\n    \"Switching Cost\", \"Implementation Effort\", \"Time to Realise Savings\",\n    \"Conflict\"\n]\n\nos.makedirs(os.path.dirname(OUT), exist_ok=True)\nwith open(OUT, \"w\", newline=\"\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n    writer = csv.DictWriter(f, fieldnames=fieldnames)\n    writer.writeheader()\n    writer.writerows(results)\n\nprint(f\"CSV written → {OUT}\")\n\n# ── summary statistics ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nfrom collections import Counter\n\nscore_dist = Counter(r[\"Score\"] for r in results)\nconflict_rows = [r for r in results if r[\"Conflict\"] == \"Y\"]\n\nprint(\"\\n=== SCORE DISTRIBUTION ===\")\nfor s in [5, 4, 3, 2, 1]:\n    print(f\"  Score {s} ({SCORE_LABELS[s]}): {score_dist.get(s, 0)}\")\n\nprint(f\"\\n=== TOTAL CONFLICTS: {len(conflict_rows)} ===\")\n\nprint(\"\\n=== CONFLICT TABLE ===\")\nhdr = f\"{'Vendor Name':<50} {'Score':>5}  {'Current Rec':<15} {'Aligned Rec':<15} {'Spend (USD)':>12}\"\nprint(hdr)\nprint(\"-\" * len(hdr))\nfor r in sorted(conflict_rows, key=lambda x: -x[\"Spend (USD)\"]):\n    print(f\"{r['Vendor Name']:<50} {r['Score']:>5}  {r['Current Recommendation']:<15} {r['Score-Aligned Recommendation']:<15} {r['Spend (USD)']:>12,.0f}\")\n\n# top 30 by spend\ntop30 = sorted(results, key=lambda x: -x[\"Spend (USD)\"])[:30]\nprint(\"\\n=== TOP 30 ROWS BY SPEND ===\")\nhdr2 = f\"{'Vendor Name':<50} {'Score':>5}  {'Label':<16} {'Current Rec':<15} {'Aligned Rec':<15} {'Conflict':>8} {'Spend (USD)':>12}\"\nprint(hdr2)\nprint(\"-\" * len(hdr2))\nfor r in top30:\n    print(f\"{r['Vendor Name']:<50} {r['Score']:>5}  {r['Score Label']:<16} {r['Current Recommendation']:<15} {r['Score-Aligned Recommendation']:<15} {r['Conflict']:>8} {r['Spend (USD)']:>12,.0f}\")\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01C88ALFtVWn8XbvFpdnSGs6","tool_input":{"file_path":"C:/Users/rjega/vendor-spend-analysis/step08_score.py","content":"import openpyxl\nimport csv\nimport os\n\n# ── paths ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nXLSX = r\"C:/Users/rjega/vendor-spend-analysis/outputs/A - TEMPLATE - RWA - Vendor Spend Strategy (R Jegadeswari).xlsx\"\nOUT  = r\"C:/Users/rjega/vendor-spend-analysis/outputs/step08_strategic_scores.csv\"\n\n# ── hard-coded score overrides ─────────────────────────────────────────────\nSCORE5 = {\n    \"salesforce uk ltd\",\n    \"amazon web services llc\",\n}\n\nSCORE4 = {\n    \"bdo llp\",\n    \"tog uk properties limited\",\n    \"cloudcrossing bvba\",\n    \"navan (tripactions inc)\",\n    \"aetna life and casualty ltd\",\n    \"zagrebtower d.o.o.\",\n    \"big frontier pty ltd (cult of monday)\",\n    \"bisley law ltd\",\n    \"cloud technology solutions ltd\",\n    \"wework singapore pte. ltd.\",\n    \"tmforum\",\n    \"hr solution international gmbh\",\n    \"jensten insurance brokers\",\n    \"telefonica global services gmbh\",\n    \"rsm uk corporate finance llp\",\n    \"infosys\",\n    \"harmonic group limited\",\n    \"4i advisory services\",\n}\n\nSCORE_LABELS = {5: \"Mission Critical\", 4: \"Strategic\", 3: \"Important\",\n                2: \"Marginal\", 1: \"Redundant\"}\n\ndef normalise(name):\n    return str(name).strip().lower() if name else \"\"\n\ndef assign_score(vendor_norm, spend_cat, suggestion, spend):\n    if vendor_norm in SCORE5:\n        return 5\n    if vendor_norm in SCORE4:\n        return 4\n\n    cat  = str(spend_cat).strip() if spend_cat else \"\"\n    sugg = str(suggestion).strip() if suggestion else \"\"\n\n    if cat == \"High Spend\" and sugg == \"Optimize\":\n        return 4\n\n    if cat == \"Medium Spend\":\n        return 3\n\n    if cat == \"Low Spend\":\n        spend_val = spend if spend else 0\n        if sugg == \"Consolidate\" and spend_val > 25000:\n            return 3\n        if (sugg == \"Consolidate\" or sugg == \"Terminate\") and 5000 <= spend_val <= 25000:\n            return 2\n\n    return 1\n\ndef switching_cost(score):\n    if score >= 4: return \"HIGH\"\n    if score == 3: return \"MEDIUM\"\n    return \"LOW\"\n\ndef impl_effort(score):\n    if score >= 4: return \"HIGH\"\n    if score == 3: return \"MEDIUM\"\n    return \"LOW\"\n\ndef time_to_savings(suggestion):\n    s = str(suggestion).strip() if suggestion else \"\"\n    if s == \"Terminate\":  return \"IMMEDIATE\"\n    if s == \"Consolidate\": return \"MEDIUM\"\n    if s == \"Optimize\":   return \"LONG\"\n    return \"MEDIUM\"\n\ndef score_aligned_rec(score):\n    if score >= 4: return \"Optimize\"\n    if score >= 2: return \"Consolidate\"\n    return \"Terminate\"\n\ndef is_conflict(current_sugg, aligned_rec, score):\n    c = str(current_sugg).strip() if current_sugg else \"\"\n    if score >= 4 and c == \"Terminate\":\n        return \"Y\"\n    if c != aligned_rec:\n        return \"Y\"\n    return \"N\"\n\n# ── read workbook ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nwb = openpyxl.load_workbook(XLSX, data_only=True)\nws = wb[\"Vendor Analysis Assessment\"]\n\nrows = list(ws.iter_rows(values_only=True))\n# find header row index\nheader_idx = None\nfor i, row in enumerate(rows):\n    if row[0] and str(row[0]).strip().lower() == \"vendor name\":\n        header_idx = i\n        break\n\nif header_idx is None:\n    raise ValueError(\"Could not find 'Vendor Name' header row\")\n\ndata_rows = rows[header_idx + 1:]\n\nresults = []\nfor row in data_rows:\n    vendor   = row[0]\n    dept     = row[1]\n    spend    = row[2]\n    desc     = row[3]\n    sugg     = row[4]\n    spend_cat= row[5]\n\n    if not vendor or str(vendor).strip() == \"\":\n        continue\n\n    v_norm = normalise(vendor)\n    spend_val = float(spend) if spend is not None else 0.0\n\n    score   = assign_score(v_norm, spend_cat, sugg, spend_val)\n    label   = SCORE_LABELS[score]\n    aligned = score_aligned_rec(score)\n    conflict= is_conflict(sugg, aligned, score)\n\n    results.append({\n        \"Vendor Name\": str(vendor).strip(),\n        \"Department\": str(dept).strip() if dept else \"\",\n        \"Spend (USD)\": spend_val,\n        \"Score\": score,\n        \"Score Label\": label,\n        \"Current Recommendation\": str(sugg).strip() if sugg else \"\",\n        \"Score-Aligned Recommendation\": aligned,\n        \"Switching Cost\": switching_cost(score),\n        \"Implementation Effort\": impl_effort(score),\n        \"Time to Realise Savings\": time_to_savings(sugg),\n        \"Conflict\": conflict,\n    })\n\nprint(f\"Total vendor rows processed: {len(results)}\")\n\n# ── write CSV ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nfieldnames = [\n    \"Vendor Name\", \"Department\", \"Spend (USD)\", \"Score\", \"Score Label\",\n    \"Current Recommendation\", \"Score-Aligned Recommendation\",\n    \"Switching Cost\", \"Implementation Effort\", \"Time to Realise Savings\",\n    \"Conflict\"\n]\n\nos.makedirs(os.path.dirname(OUT), exist_ok=True)\nwith open(OUT, \"w\", newline=\"\", encoding=\"utf-8\") as f:\n    writer = csv.DictWriter(f, fieldnames=fieldnames)\n    writer.writeheader()\n    writer.writerows(results)\n\nprint(f\"CSV written to: {OUT}\")\n\n# ── summary statistics ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nfrom collections import Counter\n\nscore_dist = Counter(r[\"Score\"] for r in results)\nconflict_rows = [r for r in results if r[\"Conflict\"] == \"Y\"]\n\nprint(\"\\n=== SCORE DISTRIBUTION ===\")\nfor s in [5, 4, 3, 2, 1]:\n    print(f\"  Score {s} ({SCORE_LABELS[s]}): {score_dist.get(s, 0)}\")\n\nprint(f\"\\n=== TOTAL CONFLICTS: {len(conflict_rows)} ===\")\n\nprint(\"\\n=== CONFLICT TABLE ===\")\nhdr = f\"{'Vendor Name':<50} {'Score':>5}  {'Current Rec':<15} {'Aligned Rec':<15} {'Spend (USD)':>12}\"\nprint(hdr)\nprint(\"-\" * len(hdr))\nfor r in sorted(conflict_rows, key=lambda x: -x[\"Spend (USD)\"]):\n    print(f\"{r['Vendor Name']:<50} {r['Score']:>5}  {r['Current Recommendation']:<15} {r['Score-Aligned Recommendation']:<15} {r['Spend (USD)']:>12,.0f}\")\n\n# top 30 by spend\ntop30 = sorted(results, key=lambda x: -x[\"Spend (USD)\"])[:30]\nprint(\"\\n=== TOP 30 ROWS BY SPEND ===\")\nhdr2 = f\"{'Vendor Name':<50} {'Score':>5}  {'Label':<16} {'Current Rec':<15} {'Aligned Rec':<15} {'Conflict':>8} {'Spend (USD)':>12}\"\nprint(hdr2)\nprint(\"-\" * len(hdr2))\nfor r in top30:\n    print(f\"{r['Vendor Name']:<50} {r['Score']:>5}  {r['Score Label']:<16} {r['Current Recommendation']:<15} {r['Score-Aligned Recommendation']:<15} {r['Conflict']:>8} {r['Spend (USD)']:>12,.0f}\")\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01GPVbm9Nn7zfuZFPd5wcVbo","tool_input":{"file_path":"C:/Users/rjega/vendor-spend-analysis/outputs/run_step08_fix.py","content":"import pandas as pd\nimport openpyxl\nfrom openpyxl.styles import Font, PatternFill, Alignment\nfrom openpyxl.utils import get_column_letter\nimport os\n\nCSV_PATH   = \"C:/Users/rjega/vendor-spend-analysis/outputs/step08_strategic_scores.csv\"\nXLSX_PATH  = \"C:/Users/rjega/vendor-spend-analysis/outputs/A - TEMPLATE - RWA - Vendor Spend Strategy (R Jegadeswari).xlsx\"\nSHEET_NAME = \"STEP08 Strategic Scores\"\n\n# ── 1. Read CSV ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\ndf = pd.read_csv(CSV_PATH)\nprint(f\"Loaded {len(df)} rows from CSV.\")\n\n# ── 2. Fix Salesforce rows ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nmask = df[\"Vendor Name\"].str.contains(\"salesforce\", case=False, na=False)\nprint(f\"\\nSalesforce rows found: {mask.sum()}\")\nprint(df.loc[mask, [\"Vendor Name\", \"Score\", \"Score Label\", \"Switching Cost\",\n                     \"Implementation Effort\", \"Current Recommendation\",\n                     \"Score-Aligned Recommendation\", \"Conflict\"]].to_string(index=False))\n\ndf.loc[mask, \"Score\"]                        = 5\ndf.loc[mask, \"Score Label\"]                  = \"Mission Critical\"\ndf.loc[mask, \"Switching Cost\"]               = \"HIGH\"\ndf.loc[mask, \"Implementation Effort\"]        = \"HIGH\"\ndf.loc[mask, \"Score-Aligned Recommendation\"] = \"Optimize\"\n# Current Recommendation for these rows is \"Optimize\" → no conflict\ndf.loc[mask, \"Conflict\"]                     = \"N\"\n\nprint(\"\\nAfter fix:\")\nprint(df.loc[mask, [\"Vendor Name\", \"Score\", \"Score Label\", \"Switching Cost\",\n                     \"Implementation Effort\", \"Current Recommendation\",\n                     \"Score-Aligned Recommendation\", \"Conflict\"]].to_string(index=False))\n\n# ── 3. Save corrected CSV ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────\ndf.to_csv(CSV_PATH, index=False)\nprint(f\"\\nCorrected CSV saved to: {CSV_PATH}\")\n\n# ── 4. Score distribution ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nprint(\"\\n── Score Distribution ─────────────────────────────────\")\nprint(df[\"Score\"].value_counts().sort_index().to_string())\n\n# ── 5. Total conflicts ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\ntotal_conflicts = (df[\"Conflict\"] == \"Y\").sum()\nprint(f\"\\nTotal Conflict = Y rows: {total_conflicts}\")\n\n# ── 6. Conflict rows sorted by Spend descending ────────────────────────────────\nprint(\"\\n── All Conflict = Y rows (sorted by Spend desc) ───────\")\nconflict_df = df[df[\"Conflict\"] == \"Y\"].sort_values(\"Spend (USD)\", ascending=False)\nprint(conflict_df[[\"Vendor Name\", \"Department\", \"Spend (USD)\", \"Score\",\n                    \"Current Recommendation\", \"Score-Aligned Recommendation\"]].to_string(index=False))\n\n# ── 7. Open Excel workbook ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nprint(f\"\\nOpening workbook: {XLSX_PATH}\")\nwb = openpyxl.load_workbook(XLSX_PATH)\nprint(f\"Existing sheets: {wb.sheetnames}\")\n\n# ── 8. Delete existing sheet if present ───────────────────────────────────────\nif SHEET_NAME in wb.sheetnames:\n    del wb[SHEET_NAME]\n    print(f\"Deleted existing sheet: '{SHEET_NAME}'\")\n\n# ── 9. Create new sheet and write data ────────────────────────────────────────\nws = wb.create_sheet(title=SHEET_NAME)\nprint(f\"Created new sheet: '{SHEET_NAME}'\")\n\nHEADERS = [\n    \"Vendor Name\", \"Department\", \"Spend (USD)\", \"Score\", \"Score Label\",\n    \"Current Recommendation\", \"Score-Aligned Recommendation\",\n    \"Switching Cost\", \"Implementation Effort\",\n    \"Time to Realise Savings\", \"Conflict\"\n]\n\n# Write header row\nfor col_idx, header in enumerate(HEADERS, start=1):\n    ws.cell(row=1, column=col_idx, value=header)\n\n# Write data rows\nfor row_idx, row in enumerate(df[HEADERS].itertuples(index=False), start=2):\n    for col_idx, value in enumerate(row, start=1):\n        ws.cell(row=row_idx, column=col_idx, value=value)\n\nprint(f\"Written {len(df)} data rows + 1 header row to sheet.\")\n\n# ── 10. Formatting ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# Bold header\nheader_font   = Font(bold=True, name=\"Calibri\", size=11)\nheader_fill   = PatternFill(fill_type=\"solid\", fgColor=\"1F4E79\")   # dark navy\nheader_font2  = Font(bold=True, name=\"Calibri\", size=11, color=\"FFFFFF\")\n\nfor col_idx in range(1, len(HEADERS) + 1):\n    cell = ws.cell(row=1, column=col_idx)\n    cell.font      = header_font2\n    cell.fill      = header_fill\n    cell.alignment = Alignment(horizontal=\"center\", vertical=\"center\", wrap_text=True)\n\n# Auto-size columns (approximate)\ncol_widths = {\n    1: 40,   # Vendor Name\n    2: 25,   # Department\n    3: 14,   # Spend (USD)\n    4:  7,   # Score\n    5: 18,   # Score Label\n    6: 22,   # Current Recommendation\n    7: 26,   # Score-Aligned Recommendation\n    8: 16,   # Switching Cost\n    9: 22,   # Implementation Effort\n   10: 22,   # Time to Realise Savings\n   11: 10,   # Conflict\n}\nfor col_idx, width in col_widths.items():\n    ws.column_dimensions[get_column_letter(col_idx)].width = width\n\nws.row_dimensions[1].height = 30\n\n# Freeze top row\nws.freeze_panes = \"A2\"\nprint(\"Applied formatting: bold header, freeze pane at A2, column widths set.\")\n\n# ── 11. Save workbook ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nwb.save(XLSX_PATH)\nprint(f\"Workbook saved: {XLSX_PATH}\")\n\nprint(\"\\nDONE\")\n"}},{"tool_name":"Write","tool_use_id":"toolu_01DB6r8dCLyhG6tLT6k65nQf","tool_input":{"file_path":"C:/Users/rjega/vendor-spend-analysis/outputs/run_step08_fix.py","content":"import pandas as pd\nimport openpyxl\nfrom openpyxl.styles import Font, PatternFill, Alignment\nfrom openpyxl.utils import get_column_letter\nimport os\n\nCSV_PATH   = \"C:/Users/rjega/vendor-spend-analysis/outputs/step08_strategic_scores.csv\"\nXLSX_PATH  = \"C:/Users/rjega/vendor-spend-analysis/outputs/A - TEMPLATE - RWA - Vendor Spend Strategy (R Jegadeswari).xlsx\"\nSHEET_NAME = \"STEP08 Strategic Scores\"\n\n# ── 1. Read CSV ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\ndf = pd.read_csv(CSV_PATH)\nprint(f\"Loaded {len(df)} rows from CSV.\")\n\n# ── 2. Fix Salesforce rows ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nmask = df[\"Vendor Name\"].str.contains(\"salesforce\", case=False, na=False)\nprint(f\"\\nSalesforce rows found: {mask.sum()}\")\nprint(df.loc[mask, [\"Vendor Name\", \"Score\", \"Score Label\", \"Switching Cost\",\n                     \"Implementation Effort\", \"Current Recommendation\",\n                     \"Score-Aligned Recommendation\", \"Conflict\"]].to_string(index=False))\n\ndf.loc[mask, \"Score\"]                        = 5\ndf.loc[mask, \"Score Label\"]                  = \"Mission Critical\"\ndf.loc[mask, \"Switching Cost\"]               = \"HIGH\"\ndf.loc[mask, \"Implementation Effort\"]        = \"HIGH\"\ndf.loc[mask, \"Score-Aligned Recommendation\"] = \"Optimize\"\n# Current Recommendation for these rows is \"Optimize\" -> no conflict\ndf.loc[mask, \"Conflict\"]                     = \"N\"\n\nprint(\"\\nAfter fix:\")\nprint(df.loc[mask, [\"Vendor Name\", \"Score\", \"Score Label\", \"Switching Cost\",\n                     \"Implementation Effort\", \"Current Recommendation\",\n                     \"Score-Aligned Recommendation\", \"Conflict\"]].to_string(index=False))\n\n# ── 3. Save corrected CSV ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────\ndf.to_csv(CSV_PATH, index=False)\nprint(f\"\\nCorrected CSV saved to: {CSV_PATH}\")\n\n# ── 4. Score distribution ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nprint(\"\\n-- Score Distribution -------------------------\")\nprint(df[\"Score\"].value_counts().sort_index().to_string())\n\n# ── 5. Total conflicts ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\ntotal_conflicts = (df[\"Conflict\"] == \"Y\").sum()\nprint(f\"\\nTotal Conflict = Y rows: {total_conflicts}\")\n\n# ── 6. Conflict rows sorted by Spend descending ────────────────────────────────\nprint(\"\\n-- All Conflict = Y rows (sorted by Spend desc) ---\")\nconflict_df = df[df[\"Conflict\"] == \"Y\"].sort_values(\"Spend (USD)\", ascending=False)\nprint(conflict_df[[\"Vendor Name\", \"Department\", \"Spend (USD)\", \"Score\",\n                    \"Current Recommendation\", \"Score-Aligned Recommendation\"]].to_string(index=False))\n\n# ── 7. Open Excel workbook ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nprint(f\"\\nOpening workbook: {XLSX_PATH}\")\nwb = openpyxl.load_workbook(XLSX_PATH)\nprint(f\"Existing sheets: {wb.sheetnames}\")\n\n# ── 8. Delete existing sheet if present ───────────────────────────────────────\nif SHEET_NAME in wb.sheetnames:\n    del wb[SHEET_NAME]\n    print(f\"Deleted existing sheet: '{SHEET_NAME}'\")\n\n# ── 9. Create new sheet and write data ────────────────────────────────────────\nws = wb.create_sheet(title=SHEET_NAME)\nprint(f\"Created new sheet: '{SHEET_NAME}'\")\n\nHEADERS = [\n    \"Vendor Name\", \"Department\", \"Spend (USD)\", \"Score\", \"Score Label\",\n    \"Current Recommendation\", \"Score-Aligned Recommendation\",\n    \"Switching Cost\", \"Implementation Effort\",\n    \"Time to Realise Savings\", \"Conflict\"\n]\n\n# Write header row\nfor col_idx, header in enumerate(HEADERS, start=1):\n    ws.cell(row=1, column=col_idx, value=header)\n\n# Write data rows\nfor row_idx, row in enumerate(df[HEADERS].itertuples(index=False), start=2):\n    for col_idx, value in enumerate(row, start=1):\n        ws.cell(row=row_idx, column=col_idx, value=value)\n\nprint(f\"Written {len(df)} data rows + 1 header row to sheet.\")\n\n# ── 10. Formatting ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nheader_fill  = PatternFill(fill_type=\"solid\", fgColor=\"1F4E79\")\nheader_font  = Font(bold=True, name=\"Calibri\", size=11, color=\"FFFFFF\")\n\nfor col_idx in range(1, len(HEADERS) + 1):\n    cell = ws.cell(row=1, column=col_idx)\n    cell.font      = header_font\n    cell.fill      = header_fill\n    cell.alignment = Alignment(horizontal=\"center\", vertical=\"center\", wrap_text=True)\n\ncol_widths = {\n    1: 40, 2: 25, 3: 14, 4: 7, 5: 18,\n    6: 22, 7: 26, 8: 16, 9: 22, 10: 22, 11: 10,\n}\nfor col_idx, width in col_widths.items():\n    ws.column_dimensions[get_column_letter(col_idx)].width = width\n\nws.row_dimensions[1].height = 30\n\n# Freeze top row\nws.freeze_panes = \"A2\"\nprint(\"Applied formatting: bold header, dark navy fill, freeze pane at A2, column widths set.\")\n\n# ── 11. Save workbook ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nwb.save(XLSX_PATH)\nprint(f\"Workbook saved: {XLSX_PATH}\")\n\nprint(\"\\nDONE\")\n"}}],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"e770ff7b-dea4-459c-8600-cb8cd066c74e"}
